---
import PortalLayout from '../../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="Graduate Diploma (Tier 3) — Sohma Institute"
  description="18-month program integrating research and clinical practice across multiple divisions. University Master's articulation pathway."
>
  <article class="tier-page">

    <!-- AT A GLANCE -->
    <header class="tier-header">
      <div class="section-label">Tier 3</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Graduate Diploma</h1>

      <div class="glance-strip">
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Duration</span>
          <span class="glance-val">18 months</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Mode</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Research + Clinical Integration</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Credential</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Graduate Diploma</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Divisions</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Minimum two integrated</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>Practitioners who want to work at complexity — patients who don't fit neatly into one division's framework. Also for those heading toward research contribution or academic partnership. If you've completed Tier 2 and find yourself wanting to draw on multiple frameworks simultaneously, this is where that integration becomes formal.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- WHAT YOU'LL LEARN -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>What you'll learn</h2>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Cross-Divisional Clinical Reasoning</h3>
          <p>How to integrate two or more divisional frameworks for complex cases. The patient with chronic pain who needs herbal intervention, functional diagnostics, and somatic therapy simultaneously — this tier teaches you to hold all of that.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Research Methodology</h3>
          <p>Whole-systems research design, n-of-1 trials, practice-based evidence methodology. You learn to generate knowledge appropriate to the complexity of the interventions, not force complex interventions into reductionist trial designs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Original Research Contribution</h3>
          <p>Required. This could be a case series, systematic review, or protocol validation study. Not a thesis in the traditional sense — the Institute values research that feeds directly back into clinical practice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- RESEARCH COMPONENT -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Research component</h2>
      <p>Your research contribution enters the Institute's research-to-bedside pipeline. A case series on herbal management of complex autoimmune presentation might become a Tier C investigational protocol. A systematic review of cannabis dosing for neuropathic pain might refine an existing Tier B provisional protocol. The research isn't academic exercise — it has a destination.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- UNIVERSITY ARTICULATION -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>University articulation</h2>
      <p>This tier articulates into Master's programs through partner institutions. The Graduate Diploma provides credit toward postgraduate study, creating a pathway from RTO-based clinical training into university research and academic careers. Specific articulation agreements and partner universities will be published as they are formalised.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- DELIVERY -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Delivery structure</h2>
      <div class="delivery-grid">
        <div class="delivery-block">
          <div class="delivery-tag">Asynchronous</div>
          <h3>Research & Study</h3>
          <p>Advanced cross-divisional content, research methodology modules, literature review, and independent research work. The self-directed component scales significantly at this tier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="delivery-block">
          <div class="delivery-tag accent">Synchronous</div>
          <h3>Clinical Integration & Supervision</h3>
          <p>Complex case conferencing across divisions, research supervision, peer review sessions. Synchronous time is reserved for the work that benefits most from real-time interaction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- PREREQUISITES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <p>Advanced Diploma (Tier 2). Demonstrated competency in at least one division through clinical portfolio and supervisor endorsement.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- PATHWAY FORWARD -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Pathway forward</h2>
      <div class="pathway-cards">
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><polyline points="19 12 12 19 5 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Tier 4 Fellowship Application</h3>
          <p>Completion qualifies for application to the Fellowship program — the Institute's highest credential and the path to clinical leadership.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Publishing Pipeline</h3>
          <p>Research output contributes to the Institute's publishing arm. Case series, systematic reviews, and protocol validation studies enter the Journal of Traditional &amp; Network Medicine or the Protocol Monograph Series.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/><path d="M6 12v5c3 3 8 3 12 0v-5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>University Master's Pathway</h3>
          <p>Credit toward postgraduate study at partner institutions. The bridge between clinical RTO training and academic research careers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- FEES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Fees & funding</h2>
      <p>Tuition fees, payment plan options, and research funding support will be published prior to the first intake. Contact the Institute for current information.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="tier-cta">
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="#" class="cta-primary">Apply Now</a>
        <a href="#" class="cta-secondary">Enquire</a>
        <a href="/education" class="cta-secondary">Back to all programs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .tier-page { font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif; color: var(--text-heading); padding: 0 clamp(24px, 4vw, 56px); }
  .tier-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .tier-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .tier-page h1, .tier-page h2, .tier-page h3 { margin: 0; }
  .section-label { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--accent-dark); margin-bottom: 1rem; white-space: nowrap; }
  .section-label::after { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--accent-line); }
  .tier-header { padding: 4rem 0 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-heading); line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 2rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .glance-strip { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .glance-item { padding: 0 1.5rem; } .glance-item:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  .glance-key { display: block; font-size: 0.5625rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .glance-val { display: block; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); }
  .glance-divider { width: 1px; height: 36px; background: var(--border-medium); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .tier-section { padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-card); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .tier-section h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .tier-section p { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-body-70); line-height: 1.8; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .content-card { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .content-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .content-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }
  .delivery-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .delivery-block { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .delivery-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.5625rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-tertiary); border: 1px solid var(--border-medium); border-radius: 2px; padding: 2px 8px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .delivery-tag.accent { color: var(--accent-dark); border-color: var(--accent-border-20); }
  .delivery-block h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .delivery-block p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }
  .pathway-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  .pathway-card { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .pathway-icon { color: var(--accent-dark); opacity: 0.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .pathway-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .pathway-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }
  .tier-cta { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-primary { font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: #fff; background: var(--accent-dark); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .cta-primary:hover { background: var(--accent-darker-hover); }
  .cta-secondary { font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--glass-12); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px; text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s; }
  .cta-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent-border-30); color: var(--accent-dark); }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .glance-strip { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; }
    .glance-divider { width: 60px; height: 1px; } .glance-item { padding: 0; }
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .delivery-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pathway-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
